 :tx/rationale "CRITICAL DISCOVERY: CCE pipeline is 50% dead code. Eight kernel functions — crystallize_concepts, update_centroid, update_centroid_weighted, concept_to_datoms, membership_datoms, should_split, should_merge, surprise_weight — are NEVER called from the CLI. The observe command writes :exploration/concept Ref and :exploration/surprise datoms when an observation matches a concept, but NEVER updates the concept itself: no centroid update, no member-count increment, no total-weight accumulation, no variance recomputation. The harvest command NEVER calls crystallize_concepts — new concepts cannot form from uncategorized observations. The status command NEVER calls should_split/should_merge — concepts cannot restructure. CONSEQUENCE: The CCE is a static concept LOOKUP against the 5 innate schemas, not a learning system. Concepts never grow, evolve, split, merge, or emerge. The entire CCE-2 (concept formation), CCE-2b (surprise-weighted centroids), and the developmental trajectory (sensorimotor → concrete operational → formal operational) are spec-complete in the kernel but unwired in the CLI. This is not a hash-embedder-vs-model2vec problem. Even with perfect semantic embeddings, the system would assign observations to static innate concepts but never: (1) update the concept centroid to reflect new members, (2) form new emergent concepts from clusters of uncategorized observations, (3) split concepts that become too broad, (4) merge concepts that converge. The SEMANTIC-EMBED EPIC addresses the FIRST bottleneck (concept assignment quality). This discovery reveals the SECOND bottleneck: concept lifecycle is completely unwired."
